    "narrative": "LawDog\u2019s optimal lineup for April 16th is anchored by **Lawrence Butler** (72.92), who presents the day's highest upside. His favorable matchup against Leiter (4.43 xERA) in a hitter-friendly environment, bolstered by a 10% park factor bump, makes him an essential start despite hitting seventh. He is joined by **Cal Raleigh** (69.89) and **Tyler Freeman** (68.95), both of whom exploit excellent matchups against Walker Buehler and Ryan Weiss, respectively. **Brendan Donovan** also sees a massive boost from his projected leadoff spot and platoon advantage against Buehler, yielding a strong 66.36. We are prioritizing high-contact, high-leverage spots today, though we remain wary of the weather in the **Taylor Ward** and **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** contest, where a 44% rain risk could compress their actual plate appearances.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was **Jung Hoo Lee** (45.03). While his projected efficiency hovered near our 40-point floor, the scarcity of stolen bases in our current 5x5 build necessitates prioritizing higher-floor starters. We opted to roll with **Wenceel Perez** (51.46) over **Jung Hoo Lee** because of **Wenceel Perez**\u2019s superior park factor and platoon edge against Bubic, despite **Wenceel Perez** batting lower in the order. Elsewhere, **Gleyber Torres** remains a high-confidence start; his leadoff assignment against Bubic is a prime opportunity to capitalize on his 13% platoon boost. We continue to monitor the status of **Yainer Diaz**, **Cal Raleigh**, **Brendan Donovan**, **Tyler Freeman**, and **Taylor Ward**, as their scores are contingent on confirmed lineup placement; should any of these bats move significantly down the order, their daily efficiency scores will be reassessed.",
